mapproperties.key: This GUI initialization code is in fact code for creating a separated GUI, but it is not the way it should be done. Instead, files permsrc/ingenenias/jade/components/GUIApp.java and permsrc/ingenenias/jade/components/GUIAppImp.java, should be customized to obtain the same effect. In concrete, the graphic component should be created within the constructor. Nevertheless, inside the constructor, the agent ID will not be available. Therefore, it is recommended a combination of both methods, i.e., including in this component an invocation of concrete methods inside the GUIApp (GUIAppImp is hidden to the implementation) that lead to the proper initialization of the graphic elements inside GUIAppImp
To enact thid diagram, it must be included inside of a packaged named "Sytem initialization".

With this, the application is associated to a component indicating what kind of pattern (multiple instances or singleton) is used. Singleton means one instance of the application is shared across several instances of agents. Multiple instances means each agent has access only to a unique personal instance. File field is left blank on purpose inside the component.
Code to print a message in the standard output

Each instance of a GUIAgent will be linked to an instance of a GUI application. Depending on the selected pattern (see components diagram), there will be one instance per agent or same instance shared across several agents.
The agent is expected to receive instances of SampleGUIEvents.
This deployment defines three agents with the same initial mental state. If a DeploymentPackageByTypeMSEntity is used, each set of instances can be concreted with a custom mental state.
